Point of Departure.definition: The lowest concentration of a chemical in a study or group of studies that produce statistically or biologically significant increases in frequency or severity of adverse effects between the exposed population and its appropriate control.

NOAEL is identified from a critical study; highest dose tested which did not the critical toxic effect in the test specied; this level then undergoes adjustments; the current and more generally accepted procedure is Bench Mark Dose (BMD); DOD uses NOAEL in other contexts such as soil screening values.
